U.S. House Speaker Jim Wright said hewould question President Reagan tomorrow about his plan toprotect Kuwaiti oil tankers with U.S. warships from attacks byIran in the Gulf.    House and Senate Democrats, who control Congress, have beencritical of Reagan's plan but have not decided how or if theyshould try to pass legislation to prohibit it.    Wright, a Texas Democrat, told reporters the Administrationhad gone ahead with plans to reflag the Kuwaiti tankers as U.S.ships without asking Congressional leaders for their advice. Reuter&#3;